				<div class="story-intro format-l">
    <div class="summary pos-vertical-bottom pos-horizontal-bleed opacity-50 ">
        <header>
                        <h1 class="ev-magazine-layout-title">How US and North Korea could stumble into World War III</h1>
                        <p class="subhead">US military planners are increasingly concerned that tensions on the Korean peninsula could unintentionally trigger a wider war as Trump and Kim Jong Un hurl unusually personal attacks online.</p>
                    </header>
        
<footer class="meta">
			<p>
			By			<span class="byline">
				<span class="vcard"><a rel="author" class="url fn" href="https://www.politico.eu/author/bryan-bender/">Bryan Bender</a></span> <span>and</span> <span class="vcard"><a rel="author" class="url fn" href="https://www.politico.eu/author/jacqueline-klimas/">Jacqueline Klimas</a></span>			</span>
		</p>
		<p class="timestamp"><time datetime="2018-01-06T16:42:27+01:00">1/6/18, 4:42 PM CET</time></p>
			<p class="updated">Updated <time datetime="2018-01-09T04:48:14+01:00">1/9/18, 4:48 AM CET</time></p>
		</footer><!--/.meta-->
    </div>
    <figure class="art"><div class="fig-graphic"><div class="photo-wrapper"><div class="photo-article"><img src="https://g8fip1kplyr33r3krz5b97d1-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/GettyImages-881258254-e1515253184632-1160x752.jpg" class="img-responsive featured-img"></div></div></div><figcaption><p>In Seoul, people watch television news covering Donald Trump and Kim Jong Un&#039;s spat | Jung yeon Je/AFP via Getty Images</p></figcaption></figure></div><!-- /.story-intro.fomat-l -->
    <figcaption class="story-intro"><p>In Seoul, people watch television news covering Donald Trump and Kim Jong Un&#039;s spat | Jung yeon Je/AFP via Getty Images</p></figcaption>
